claim.claim-text:
1. An optical communication module comprising: (a) a plurality of electroconductive media each of which: (a1) has a plurality of electroconductive pins; (a2) forms a multilayer structure with the other electroconductive medium or media; and (a3) protrudes from the main body of the optical communication module;
(b) at least one optoelectronic device selected from the group consisting of at least one light-emitting device and at least one light-receiving device, the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device being supported by one of the electroconductive media; (c) an electric-circuit part being: (c1) supported by one of the electroconductive media; and (c2) connected to the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device; and
(d) an optically coupling means being: (d1) supported by one of the electroconductive media; and (d2) coupled optically with the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device.

11. An optical communication module as defined in claim 10, being further defined by that: 
(a) the electroconductive media are two layers of lead frames; 
(b) the optically coupling means or each optically coupling means is an optical fiber; 
(e) the LD or each LD and the optical fiber or each optical fiber coupled optically with the LD or each LD are supported by a part of a first lead frame; 
(d) the driver IC or each driver IC is supported by a part of a second lead frame; 
(e) the PD or each PD and the optical fiber or each optical fiber coupled optically with the PD or each PD are supported by the remaining part of the first lead frame; 
(f) the signal amplifier or each signal amplifier is supported by the remaining part of the second lead frame; 
(g) the combination or each combination of the LD, the optical fiber coupled optically with the LD, and the driver IC forms a signal-transmitting portion; 
(h) the combination or each combination of the PD, the optical fiber coupled optically with the PD, and the signal amplifier forms a signal-receiving portion; 
(i) the optical communication module further comprises a resin-molding portion enclosing the signal-transmitting portion and the signal-receiving portion for forming a package; and 
(j) the connector portion protrudes from the package.

12. An optical communication module as defined in claim 1, being further defined by that: 
(a) there are two layers of the electroconductive media; 
(b) the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device is supported by a first electroconductive medium; 
(c) the electric-circuit part or each electric-circuit part is supported by the second electroconductive medium; and 
(d) the module further comprises an electric insulator sandwiched between the first and second electroconductive media.

16. An optical communication module as defined in claim 12, being further defined by that: 
(a) the module further comprises at least one Si platform; 
(b) the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device is supported by the first electroconductive medium through the Si platform or each Si platform; 
(c) the electric-circuit part or each electric-circuit part is supported directly by the second electroconductive medium; and 
(d) the electric insulator has a thermal insulation property.

19. An optical communication module as defined in claim 12, wherein: 
(a) the light-emitting device or each light-emitting device is an LD; 
(b) the electric-circuit part or each electric-circuit part connected to the LD or each LD is a driver IC; 
(c) the light-receiving device or each light-receiving device is a PD; and 
(d) the electric-circuit part or each electric-circuit part connected to the PD or each PD is a signal amplifier.

21. An optical communication module comprising: 
(a) a plurality of electroconductive media each of which: 
(a1) has a plurality of electroconductive pins; 
(a2) forms a multilayer structure with the other electroconductive medium or media; and 
(a3) protrudes from the main body of the optical communication module; 

(b) a light-emitting device and a light-receiving device that are supported by one of the electroconductive media; 
(c) an electric-circuit part being: 
(c1) supported by one of the electroconductive media; and 
(c2) connected to each of the light-emitting device and the light-receiving device; 

(d) an optical wavelength demultiplexer supported by one of the electroconductive media; 
(e) an optical fiber being: 
(e1) supported by one of the electroconductive media; and 
(e2) coupled optically with the light-emitting device and the light-receiving device through the optical wavelength demultiplexer; and 

(f) a connector portion that: 
(f1) is formed at the end portion of each of the electroconductive media; and 
(f2) is to be connected to the next-stage circuit substrate.

23. A method of connecting an optical communication module with the next-stage circuit substrate, the method comprising the steps of: 
(a) providing an optical communication module comprising: 
(a1) a multiple layers of electroconductive media; 
(a2) at least one optoelectronic device selected from the group consisting of at least one light-emitting device and at least one light-receiving device, the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device being supported by one of the electroconductive media; 
(a3) an electric-circuit part connected to the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device, the electric-circuit part or each electric-circuit part being supported by one of the electroconductive media; 
(a4) an optically coupling means coupled optically with the optoelectronic device or each optoelectronic device, the optically coupling means or each optically coupling means being supported by one of the electroconductive media; and 
(a5) a connector portion formed at the end portion of each of the electroconductive media; 

(b) forming solder bumps at a connecting portion of the next-stage circuit substrate to be connected with the optical communication module; 
(c) fitting the connecting portion of the next-stage circuit substrate between the connector portions of the optical communication module; and 
(d) connecting the fitted portion by soldering accompanied by non-contact heating.
